Hi there,





Â 
Today, Headstarter has a community of over 115,000 engineers. Of the 3,000 whoâ€™ve listed Headstarter on their LinkedIn, 72% are
currently employed at companies like Google, Amazon, Microsoft, and other top startups. Our mission has always stayed the same,
which is to continue surfacing high-signal opportunities that most engineers wonâ€™t find on their own.
Â 
Thatâ€™s why we just launched BuildCore, a new two-week sprint for experienced engineers to work directly with founders from some of
the most ambitious startups in Silicon Valley and NYC.
Â 
Itâ€™s free, selective (~5% acceptance), and designed to fast-track you to a full-time role at a top-tier startup.
Â 
Over the past year, weâ€™ve been quietly building a recruiting pipeline for the top 1% of startups to hire through Headstarter. One
founder, letâ€™s call him â€œHallâ€ left Xai (Grok) as a tech lead, came to Headstarter while in stealth, and built his first
engineering team through us. Heâ€™s now in a top SF accelerator with seed funding lined up from top VCs.
Â 
This is the caliber of company youâ€™ll be working with in BuildCore.
Â 
Youâ€™ll ship real projects sponsored by early-stage startups. Learn from world-class engineers, product leads, and technical
founders. Get seen by hiring managers who are scaling fast and looking for people like you.
Â 
No fluff. No costs.
Â 
BuildCore kicks off this summer. Just two weeks of high-signal work in a curated cohort and a pipeline to full-time offers.
Â 
Weâ€™re running two cohorts this summer.
Â 
Spots are limited. Applications are now open here [http://apply.headstarter.co/?refem6.17].
Â 
Best,
Sara

subject: Made with love: On craft, quality, and connection in the AI era
body:
The Long & Short of It

By Figma


By Figma

    
    
    Read this article on LinkedIn to join the conversation
Read on LinkedIn
https://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/made-love-craft-quality-connection-ai-era-figma-qtvne?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BSoOST7V6SLqrOhw9jXb%2FQA%3D%3D&midToken=AQEGTZsEbwA4Fg&midSig=166iinxHsN5bQ1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_-null-j5vpgy~mbzt2nox~k8-null-null&eid=j5vpgy-mbzt2nox-k8&otpToken=MTMwNDFiZTgxNTJkY2RjM2IzMmUwZmViNDExYmU3YjU4ZGNmZDM0Njk5YWU4ZjZmN2JjZjA2Njk0ODUzNTlmM2YwZDNkNWU5NzRlY2RhZTg1Yjg3ZDJjMTVlYjhkY2EyNmQ4YzRmMTM5Y2ZjYjNmYzI1Zjk0ZGRjLDEsMQ%3D%3D
  
AI may be changing how we work, but itâ€™s definitely not changing the importance of making good work. With new AI products and capabilities coming out every week, designers and builders are getting savvier about how to build with craft and quality standards in mind. More than ever, theyâ€™re using AI not just for automation, but artistryâ€”and not just for function, but feeling. Make it happen With Figma Make, our new prompt-to-code tool, you can use natural language or any static design to create an interactive prototype. Thereâ€™s no limit to what you can make, or when you can use it in your process. Here are some of our favorite tips for making the most of Figma Makeâ€”prompts and all. Read more Connect to context Without context, agentic coding tools can only get you so far. As more people get serious about applying AI to their real work, getting that context matters more than ever. The Figma Dev Mode MCP server brings design context directly from Figma files into AI coding tools, giving LLMs access to variables, components, and styles to better capture design intent. Read more Show you care Picking a therapist is tough. Picking an AI mental health companion is even trickier. Knowing this, Headspace put trust and safety first when shaping Ebb. From naming the character to setting conversational guidelines, hereâ€™s how they kept the AI visible while making sure users felt supported. Read more It takes practice What does it take to master your craft? Practice, our third annual print publication for Config, offers some answers. Browse the digital version here, or check out the microsite we created with design studio Other Means to download the custom font by Kia Tasbihgou.
